    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-03T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="895"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d895">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363 Manchuria/189: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-03T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 3, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>104. Department’s 102, May 2, 9 p.m. For your information and, in your
                    discretion, oral transmission to the Foreign Office.</p>
                <p>On May 2 American Embassy, Tokyo, telegraphed Department to the effect that as
                    there exists between American and British oil interests no divergence of view in
                    regard to scope of offer and method of presentation, Standard-Vacuum and Rising
                    Sun will follow procedure outlined in Department’s telegram to Tokyo of April 24
                    (see Department’s 96, April 26, 7 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d895fn2">See footnote
                        1, <ref target="#pg_911">p. 911</ref>.</note>).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
